OL,3,C'I spoke for my constituents who have
OL,4,Cno voice': Party-suspended MP speaks
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FShe added she was "deeply saddened" to
OL,8,Fhave had the whip removed, but voted
OL,9,Fas "a strict matter of conscience".
OL,11,FMs Long-Bailey said: "As an MP in
OL,12,FSalford, where 44.7% of children live
OL,13,Fin poverty with some wards closer to
OL,14,F60%, I urged the Government in the
OL,15,FKing's Speech debate to scrap the two-
OL,16,Fchild limit on Universal Credit.
OL,18,F"This is something many struggling
OL,19,Ffamilies have raised with me but it's
OL,20,Falso something that every child
OL,21,Fpoverty expert has called for.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
