OL,3,C'I spoke for my constituents who have
OL,4,Cno voice': Party-suspended MP speaks
OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FKeir Starmer has been under mounting
OL,8,Fpressure to scrap the policy, which
OL,9,Frestricts child welfare payments to
OL,10,Fthe first two children born in most
OL,11,Ffamilies with some exceptions.The
OL,12,Fprime minister and his cabinet say the
OL,13,Fstate of the public finances means
OL,14,Fthey cannot afford to abolish the
OL,15,Fbenefit limit without economic growth.
OL,17,FSpeaking in interviews on Monday, the
OL,18,FEducation Secretary Bridget Phillipson
OL,19,Fsignalled a softening of the
OL,20,Fgovernment's position on the policy.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
